==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek ''[[Ελισαβετ]]'' (''Elisabet''), a transliteration of the Hebrew ''אֱלִישֶׁבַע'' ('Elisheva''), meaning ''my [[God]] is an oath''.

===Proper noun===
'''Elizabeth'''

# A female [[given name]]
# The mother of John the Baptist

